original: Belfrage, Rolf Harald, praktiserande läkare, Göteborg, f. 27/12/94 i Gbg av med. dr Fritz B. o. Hildur Inge-(borg Tranéus. G. 23i m. Ingrid Almqvist. Barn: Hans f. 24, med. stud., Christian 27, teknolog. — Stud :ex. i Gbg 13, med. kand. i Upps. 17, med. lic. i Sthlm 22. E. läk. v. Kronpr. Lovisas vårdanst. samt Sthlms epid:-sjukh. 22, aman. o. bitr. läk. v. Gbgs barnsjukh. 23-26, prakt. läk. i Gbg sed. 26, läk. v. Mjölkdroppen där sed. 27, skolläk. v. Gbgs v. realsk. 28-34 o. v. Vasa h. a. 1. sed. 34, bitr. läk. v. Gbgs tub idispensär sed. 29. Skr.: art. på olika omr.
translated: Belfrage, Rolf Harald, practicing physician, Gothenburg, b. December 27, 1894 in Gothenburg to medical doctor Fritz B. and Hildur Ingeborg Tranéus. Married in 1923 to Ingrid Almqvist. Children: Hans b. 1924, studying medicine, Christian b. 1927, studying technology. He received his studentexamen in Gothenburg in 1913, his Bachelor of Medicine degree in Uppsala in 1917, and his medical license in Stockholm in 1922. He worked as a doctor at Kronprinsessan Lovisa's care facility and Stockholm's epidemic hospital in 1922, as an assistant and attending physician at Gothenburg's children's hospital from 1923-1926, and has been a practicing physician in Gothenburg since 1926. He has also worked as a doctor at Mjölkdroppen since 1927, as a school physician at Gothenburg's higher elementary school from 1928-1934, and at Vasa högre allmänna läroverk since 1934. He has also worked as an assistant physician at Gothenburg's tuberculosis dispensary since 1929. He has written articles on various topics.
